 is interesting. Never thought about it this way. BTW, i like the new comment system.</p></div><div class="comment-actions"> <a href="http://mashable.com/2011/04/26/scooters-environmental-infographic/#comment-17279201" class="comment-timestamp"><time datetime="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 16:44:41 -0400">April 26, 2011 16:44:41</time> </a> <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/04/26/scooters-environmental-infographic/?replytocom=17279201#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-17279201", "17279201", "respond", "599673")'>Reply</a> <a href="/follow/comments/4db72ec95198401262003084/vote?v=1" class='vote vote-up ' data-remote="" data-method="PUT">1</a> <a href="/follow/comments/4db72ec95198401262003084/flag" class="flag ">Flag this comment</a></div></div><ul class='children'><li class="comment byuser comment-author-jolie-odell bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-17279491"><hr /><div id="comment-17279491" class="comment-wrapper "><div class="comment-author vcard"><div class="comment-avatar "> <a href="/follow/people/jolie/" data-badges="6" data-followers="2118"> <img class='avatar avatar-50 photo' src='http://6.mshcdn.com/follow/uploads/user/avatar/9d/d1/84/af/d3/d7/thumb_jolie-o-dell-7ef56f23db.jpg' /> </a></div><span class='author-link'><a href='/follow/people/jolie/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Jolie O'Dell</a></span> <a href="/follow/people/jolie/follow/" class="follow_button" data-badges="6" data-followers="2118">Follow</a> <a href="/follow/people/jolie/badges"> <img src="/follow/images/new_badges/12/mashable_staff_16x16.png" class="badge" /> </a></div><div class="comment-body"><p>Heh, thanks! Most users (in general and for all web apps) really hate any change, so it&#8217;s nice to see some praise for the new system.  =)</p></div><div class="comment-actions"> <a href="http://mashable.com/2011/04/26/scooters-environmental-infographic/#comment-17279491" class="comment-timestamp"><time datetime="Tue, 26 Apr 2011 18:29:52 -0400">